This paper deals with text classification using a hybrid approach of recurrent neural network (RNN) and nearest neighbor methods. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses machine learning models and their training, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with query-time reduction, which is a common problem in Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The use of RNNs and nearest neighbor methods also suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV), as these methods are commonly used in these fields.
